      <a class="anchor" id="users.authenticate"></a>
<div class="method-title">Authenticates a user</div>
      <h5>Example request</h5>
          <pre><code class="javascript">
//Authenticates a user given email and password
marketcloud.users.authenticate('john.snow@wall.com','IKnowNothing')
.then(function(data){
  // Your code here
})
                
})      
      </code></pre>
      <p>If the authentication is successful, <code>data</code> is an object:</p>
        <pre><code class="json">
{
  "user" : {
    "email" : "john.doe@example.com",
    "full_name" : "John Doe"
  },
  "token" : "SECRET_TOKEN"
}
      </code> </pre>
      <p>You can use the token to make calls on behalf of the user, but since the SDK works with admin credentials, you should avoid doing it.</p>
      
